title: Georgina Wilson, Arthur Burnand celebrate civil wedding anniversary
text:
Georgina Wilson, Arthur Burnand celebrate civil wedding anniversary Georgina reveals that she and Arthur married in Hong Kong before their wedding in the UK Published 11:19 PM, February 20, 2017 Updated 11:19 PM, February 20, 2017 CIVIL WEDDING. Georgina Wilson and husband Arthur Burnand pose with their male guests during their civil wedding one year ago. Georgina revealed on Instagram that she and Arthur married in Hong Kong before their church wedding in April 2016. Screengrab from Instagram/@ilovegeorgina 
MANILA, Philippines – Georgina Wilson surprised the public when she married British businessman Arthur Burnand in England in April 2016. But on Monday, February 20, Georgina revealed that she and Arthur also had a civil wedding in Hong Kong, two months before their church wedding. (READ: Georgina Wilson engaged to Arthur Burnand ) 
On Instagram, Georgina wrote: " Happy one year civil wedding anniversary my love [Arthur Burnand] I'm so happy I married you and I'm also so happy that I wore Alaia," referring to the Tunisian born designer, who made her dress for the civil wedding. A post shared by Georgina Wilson (@ilovegeorgina) on Feb 19, 2017 at 8:00pm PST 
She also shared group photos of those who attended, including Erwan Heussaff, Raymond Gutierrez, Adrien Semblat, Nico Bolzico, Martine Cajucom, and Bea Soriano. A post shared by Georgina Wilson (@ilovegeorgina) on Feb 19, 2017 at 8:22pm PST A post shared by Georgina Wilson (@ilovegeorgina) on Feb 19, 2017 at 8:18pm PST 
Georgina posted photos of her father and father-in-law and a photo of her and Arthur after the civil wedding. A post shared by Georgina Wilson (@ilovegeorgina) on Feb 20, 2017 at 1:07am PST A post shared by Georgina Wilson (@ilovegeorgina) on Feb 20, 2017 at 3:08am PST 
Georgia and Arthur are now parents to Archie , who was born in December 2016. – Rappler.com HOW DOES THIS STORY MAKE YOU FEEL? Happy
